OL,6,FHe also remains the only Scottish
OL,7,Fplayer to have won a Ballon d'Or,
OL,8,Fwhich he was awarded in 1964.
OL,10,FThe United legend, who started his
OL,11,Fcareer at Huddersfield and also played
OL,12,Ffor Manchester City and Torino, made
OL,13,Fhis senior Scotland debut aged 18 in
OL,14,F1958 and was capped 55 times.
OL,16,FWith 30 goals he remains joint record
OL,17,Fscorer for Scotland alongside Sir
OL,18,FKenny Dalglish.
